article.description: Maine tops William & Mary in 34-20 win
article.headline: Maine tops William & Mary in 34-20 win
article.linkText: Maine tops William & Mary in 34-20 win
article.story: ORONO, Maine -- Marcus Wasilewski passed for 192 yards and two touchdowns while leading Maine to a 34-20 win over William & Mary in a Colonial Athletic Conference game Saturday. Maine (6-1, 3-0) piled up 420 yards in total offense in its first home field win over William & Mary (4-3, 1-2) since 2002. Wasilewski, who completed 16 of 22 passes, nearly rushed for a touchdown as well but fumbled the ball on a 5-yard run in the first quarter, with lineman Bruce Johnson recovering it in the endzone to give the Black Bears their first TD of the game. Ricky Stevens rushed for another Maine TD about 7 minutes later. Damarr Aultman caught an 11-yard TD pass from Wasilewski and Justin Perillo held onto a 6-yarder. Sean Decloux kicked two field goals. Brent Caprio led William & Mary with 91 yards passing, including a 4-yard TD pass to Tre McBride.
